## Objective

In this lab, you will complete a **Snake game** on the TM4C1294XL LaunchPad using FreeRTOS. Starting from a basic working snake implementation, you will add game mechanics, proper synchronization, and event-driven coordination between tasks.

Three FreeRTOS primitives you have not used before appear in this lab:

| Primitive | Purpose in this lab |
| :-------- | :------------------ |
| **Mutex** | Protect shared game state from concurrent access |
| **Task Notifications** | Signal `vRenderTask` only when there is something new to draw |
| **Event Groups** | Coordinate game events (food eaten, game over) for audio feedback |

---

## Learning Goals

- Use a **mutex** to protect shared resources from concurrent access
- Explain the difference between a mutex and a binary semaphore
- Use **task notifications** to build event-driven rendering instead of polling
- Use an **event group** to signal multiple types of game events from one object
- Design and implement game logic by reasoning through requirements
- Build a complete embedded game incrementally

---

