| Missing | Your task |
| :------ | :-------- |
| Mutex never created or used | Step 2 |
| Render polls every 33 ms regardless of changes | Step 3 |
| No food or fruit | Step 4 |
| No score, growth, or speed scaling | Step 5 |
| No audio feedback for game events | Step 6 |
| No direction reversal prevention or self-collision | Step 7 |

### Race Conditions in the Starter (report required)

Study the source files and answer these questions in your lab report:

1. `xMutexLCD` is declared in `app_objects.h`. Where is it **defined**? Where is `xSemaphoreCreateMutex()` called? What happens at runtime if `DrawGame()` executes before the mutex exists?

2. `vSnakeTask` writes to `snake[]` and `snakeLength` while `vRenderTask` reads them at the same time. What ARM Cortex-M4 guarantee (if any) applies to multi-word struct accesses across tasks?

3. `vSnakeTask` reads `gameState.currentDirection` while `vInputTask` writes it. Is `volatile` enough to make this safe? Explain why or why not.

4. `vRenderTask` wakes every 33 ms even when the game is paused. How many unnecessary full redraws per second does this produce?

